  "description": "AdV40 (species F) complete linear dsDNA genome ~34214 bp with covalently bound terminal protein (TP, pTP-derived) at each 5' end and inverted terminal repeats (ITRs) at the ends. Tropism: enteric, paediatric gastroenteritis. Genome encodes E1A, E1B, E2A (DBP), E2B (pTP, AdPol), E3 (immune modulation), E4 (mRNA export), L1-L5 late mRNAs (capsid: hexon II, penton III, fiber IV) and VA RNAs (RNA-pol-III non-coding). Replication uses protein-priming by pTP-dCMP at the ITR origin; no host primer involved.",
